## Part 2: OAuth2/OIDC Fundamentals

### What Problem Does OAuth2 Solve?

**Before OAuth2:**
```
User ──► Third-Party App ──► Gives username/password ──► Backend
                                              │
                                              ▼
                                    App stores credentials
                                    (SECURITY NIGHTMARE)
```

**After OAuth2:**
```
User ──► Third-Party App ──► "I need access"
                              │
                              ▼
        User redirected to Auth Server ──► User logs in directly
                              │
                              ▼
        Auth Server gives TOKEN (not credentials) to App
                              │
                              ▼
        App uses token for API access (no stored passwords!)
```

### OAuth2 Grant Types (Why Authorization Code + PKCE?)

| Grant Type | Use Case | Security Level | Your Project |
|------------|----------|----------------|--------------|
| **Client Credentials** | Server-to-Server | High | ❌ Not used |
| **Resource Owner Password** | Legacy/Legacy | ⚠️ Low | ❌ Deprecated |
| **Implicit** | SPA (old) | ⚠️ Medium | ❌ Deprecated |
| **Authorization Code** | Server-side apps | High | ✅ Used |
| **Auth Code + PKCE** | Mobile/Desktop/Native | Highest | ✅ **Your choice** |

**Why PKCE (Proof Key for Code Exchange)?**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    THE ATTACK PKCE PREVENTS                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  1. Attacker intercepts authorization code redirect            │
│     (e.g., malicious app registers same deep link scheme)      │
│                                                                 │
│  2. Without PKCE:                                               │
│     Attacker ──► Sends code to token endpoint ──► Gets tokens! │
│                                                                 │
│  3. With PKCE:                                                  │
│     Attacker ──► Sends code ──► Missing code_verifier ──► ❌   │
│                                                                 │
│  The code_verifier is a secret only the legitimate app knows!  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

